attributes.Long form description: The student unscrews the 8 hex socket heads from the Knarrevik with an Allen wrench and places them on the table. Subsequently, the student removes the top table from the furniture and turns it over to remove the remaining hex socket heads from the furniture. The student removes the first leg, places it on the table, and continues by removing the remaining 3 legs. Once the legs are removed, he stacks them on the table, along with the hex socket heads and finally, the student stacks the shelf on the top table and leaves the Allen wrench on the table.

attributes.Transcription: We will now disassemble a bedside table from IKEA, so please go ahead.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the top table of the furniture.
The student disassembles the first leg of the furniture.
The student disassembles the second leg of the furniture.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should not drop the Allen wrench.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the third leg of the furniture.

attributes.Incorrect Action Explanation: The student should not drop the hex_socket_head.

attributes.Action sentence: The student disassembles the fourth leg of the shelf.
